title.narrative: PREVENTION AND SOCIAL REINSERTION OF CHILDREN

description.narrative: By 2024, institutions, organizations, families and communities of prioritized groups and territories have the knowledge and tools required for the prevention, treatment and social reintegration of children and adolescents who have committed acts that the law classifies as crimes, with aggravated behaviors and / or victims of crime., which contributes to Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2024, more girls, boys and adolescents from prioritized groups and territories benefit from comprehensive, violence-free prevention and protection services and areas.

description.narrative: Discreet results are maintained with regards to children and adolescents who commit acts classified as crimes. Support was maintained for 150 adolescents interned in Integral Education Schools run by the Ministry of the Interior and a context emergency forced UNICEF to develop strategic communications, since public attention was focused on adolescents involved in legal processes. 146 boys and 287 girls who were victims of sexual abuse or other crimes received psychological and legal accompaniment, supported by UNICEF. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:14/01/2022
